[13:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'story, a link, the hook angle, why this matters to my audience, etc., etc. That being said, transparently, we hit a couple of issues that honestly probably had to do a little bit with user error and a little bit with Claude not digging'

[13:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'deeper before building. The main issue that we hit was in this Claude managed environment, it wasn\'t able to actually access Reddit directly. And so this thing took 28 minutes to run, mostly because it kept getting errors when'

[13:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trying to access Reddit. So it actually was able to search the web and find a lot of really great relevant articles, but because it wasn\'t able to pull in the Reddit link directly, the system failed. Because if we come down here, we can see that one of the requirements was'

[14:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that each post links to a real Reddit post. And so because we weren\'t able to pull those in, the system failed. And so I did spend a lot of tokens on this. You can see I spent like 27 million tokens. It was like $12 just to run this. And'

[14:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'again, like this actually really could have been avoided had we known going into it that we would have run into these issues with Reddit. So maybe before creating the managed agent, having the system actually check the individual pieces just to make sure that the theories are good behind the build'

[14:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'before actually setting it up on the cloud. What\'s good about the system is that we have the core foundation in place. And this was sort of the whole point of running these managed agents in loop mode is that they are self-improving with every run. And with'

[14:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'each run, we learn something new about how we can make an upgrade. And so now it\'s just asking me like, how do I want to fix the Reddit sourcing issue? Can I just use web search only and this will run in like two or three minutes as opposed to 30 minutes with a better'

[14:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
